          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "59be",
          "text": "Notes on a book by Daniel Christian Wahl",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 40,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e998",
          "text": "Symptoms of systemic strain are becoming clearer every day: unprecedented weather events, growing economic inequality, political dysfunction, etc. Many of these issues can be attributed to a culture that has drawn hard lines between ourselves, other beings, and our environment for hundreds of years.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "373a",
          "text": "Designing Regenerative Cultures is an impassioned plea for awareness of our interbeing — one-ness with each other and our surroundings — and for a more systemic approach to making and measuring the effects of our actions in the world. The book offers frameworks and models for a more holistic approach to design towards the creation of truly regenerative systems.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 31,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 86,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 76,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5343",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "0*62Qqrr8uKWxFrjfE",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "dcfb",
          "text": "Wahl uses questions as a rhetorical device to encourage deeper exploration, and lists of such question-prompts are present throughout the text. For example:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b1fc",
          "text": "Q Are we weaving the appropriate synergies by valuing the degree and quality of interconnections between the different components or agents in the system?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 1,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ea2e",
          "text": "Q Are we paying enough attention to the diversity and the quality of interacting system components and their interdependence?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 1,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "97d3",
          "text": "Q Are we designing for the renewable use of vital resources (like energy and materials) on which these systems depend?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 1,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "19c4",
          "text": "Q Are we paying enough attention to the quality and speed of information that flows through these systems to enable the different components to learn from systemic feedback loops?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 1,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "BQ"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "74e6",
          "text": "These lists of questions are the heart of the book. They’re an open-ended invitation to examine our own design practices in light of our urgent need for a different approach to being in the world. The questions, plus the models, frameworks, and references to a wide body of work by researchers and practitioners in regenerative disciplines make this book a valuable resource as we pivot towards a more responsible design practice.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d4fbca71e54_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b9b0",
          "text": "This review was originally published by Jorge Arango on his website.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
